pollution_data['Timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(pollution_data['Timestamp'], errors='coerce')

                                   (pollution_data['Timestamp'].dt.year <= 2021)]

covid_period_data_clean = covid_period_data[['state', 'PM2.5']].dropna()

In [12]:
# Filter data for the year 2021 and the specified station
station_name = "Lal Bahadur Shastri Nagar, Kalaburagi - KSPCB"
pollution_2021 = pollution_data[(pollution_data['Timestamp'].dt.year == 2021) &
                                (pollution_data['station'] == station_name)]

# Remove missing PM2.5 values
pollution_2021_clean = pollution_2021[['Timestamp', 'PM2.5']].dropna()

# Extract day of the week (0=Monday, 6=Sunday) and month
pollution_2021_clean['Weekday'] = pollution_2021_clean['Timestamp'].dt.weekday
pollution_2021_clean['Month'] = pollution_2021_clean['Timestamp'].dt.month

# Categorize into Weekdays (0-4) and Weekends (5-6)
pollution_2021_clean['Day_Type'] = pollution_2021_clean['Weekday'].apply(lambda x: 'Weekday' if x < 5 else 'Weekend')

# Compute monthly average PM2.5 for weekdays and weekends separately
monthly_avg_pm25 = pollution_2021_clean.groupby(['Month', 'Day_Type'])['PM2.5'].mean().unstack()

# Plot the trends
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.plot(monthly_avg_pm25.index, monthly_avg_pm25['Weekday'], marker='o', linestyle='-', label='Weekdays', color='blue')
plt.plot(monthly_avg_pm25.index, monthly_avg_pm25['Weekend'], marker='s', linestyle='-', label='Weekends', color='red')

# Formatting the plot
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Average PM2.5 (µg/m³)')
plt.title('Monthly Average PM2.5 Levels (Weekdays vs Weekends) - 2021')
plt.xticks(ticks=range(1, 13), labels=['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun', 'Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec'])
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# Filter data for the year 2022
pollution_2022 = pollution_data[pollution_data['Timestamp'].dt.year == 2022]

# Remove missing PM2.5 values
pollution_2022_clean = pollution_2022[['state', 'Timestamp', 'PM2.5']].dropna()

# Define summer (March-May) and monsoon (June-September) months
summer_months = [3, 4, 5]
monsoon_months = [6, 7, 8, 9]

# Compute average PM2.5 levels for each state in summer and monsoon
summer_avg_pm25 = pollution_2022_clean[pollution_2022_clean['Timestamp'].dt.month.isin(summer_months)].groupby('state')['PM2.5'].mean()
monsoon_avg_pm25 = pollution_2022_clean[pollution_2022_clean['Timestamp'].dt.month.isin(monsoon_months)].groupby('state')['PM2.5'].mean()

# Calculate percentage change ((monsoon - summer) / summer * 100)
percentage_change_pm25 = ((monsoon_avg_pm25 - summer_avg_pm25) / summer_avg_pm25) * 100

# Identify the state with the most significant percentage change (increase or decrease)
max_difference_state = percentage_change_pm25.abs().idxmax()
max_difference_value = percentage_change_pm25[max_difference_state]

percentage_change_pm25, max_difference_state, max_difference_value

# Filter data for Delhi from 2017 to 2023
delhi_data = pollution_data[(pollution_data['state'] == 'Delhi') & (pollution_data['Timestamp'].dt.year.between(2017, 2023))]
delhi_data_clean = delhi_data[['Timestamp', 'PM2.5']].dropna()
winter_months = [12, 1, 2]
summer_months = [3, 4, 5]
monsoon_months = [6, 7, 8, 9]
delhi_data_clean['Season'] = delhi_data_clean['Timestamp'].dt.month.map(
    lambda m: 'Winter' if m in winter_months else ('Summer' if m in summer_months else 'Monsoon'))
delhi_data_clean['Year'] = delhi_data_clean['Timestamp'].dt.year
seasonal_avg_pm25_delhi = delhi_data_clean.groupby(['Year', 'Season'])['PM2.5'].mean().unstack()
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.plot(seasonal_avg_pm25_delhi.index, seasonal_avg_pm25_delhi['Winter'], marker='o', linestyle='-', label='Winter', color='blue')
plt.plot(seasonal_avg_pm25_delhi.index, seasonal_avg_pm25_delhi['Summer'], marker='s', linestyle='-', label='Summer', color='red')
plt.plot(seasonal_avg_pm25_delhi.index, seasonal_avg_pm25_delhi['Monsoon'], marker='^', linestyle='-', label='Monsoon', color='green')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Average PM2.5 (µg/m³)')
plt.title('Seasonal PM2.5 Levels in Delhi (2017-2023)')
plt.xticks(ticks=range(2017, 2024))
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# Filter data for Delhi and Mumbai from 2015 to 2023
cities_data = pollution_data[(pollution_data['state'].isin(['Delhi', 'Maharashtra'])) &
                             (pollution_data['Timestamp'].dt.year.between(2015, 2023))]

# Remove missing PM2.5 values
cities_data_clean = cities_data[['state', 'Timestamp', 'PM2.5']].dropna()

# Extract year and month for time-series analysis
cities_data_clean['Year-Month'] = cities_data_clean['Timestamp'].dt.to_period('M')

# Compute monthly average PM2.5 levels for both cities
cities_avg_pm25 = cities_data_clean.groupby(['Year-Month', 'state'])['PM2.5'].mean().unstack()

# Convert Year-Month back to datetime format for plotting
cities_avg_pm25.index = cities_avg_pm25.index.to_timestamp()

# Plot time-series graph
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.plot(cities_avg_pm25.index, cities_avg_pm25['Delhi'], label='Delhi', color='red', linewidth=1.5)
plt.plot(cities_avg_pm25.index, cities_avg_pm25['Maharashtra'], label='Mumbai', color='blue', linewidth=1.5)

# Formatting the plot
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Average PM2.5 (µg/m³)')
plt.title('Time-Series Comparison: PM2.5 Levels in Delhi vs. Mumbai (2015-2023)')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# Compute standard deviation (measure of fluctuation) for each city
delhi_fluctuation = cities_avg_pm25['Delhi'].std()
mumbai_fluctuation = cities_avg_pm25['Maharashtra'].std()

delhi_fluctuation, mumbai_fluctuation

# Filter data for Maharashtra and Madhya Pradesh
maha_data = merged_data[merged_data['state'] == 'Maharashtra']
mp_data = merged_data[merged_data['state'] == 'Madhya Pradesh']

# Calculate average PM2.5 levels for both states
avg_pm25_maha = maha_data['PM2.5'].mean()
avg_pm25_mp = mp_data['PM2.5'].mean()

# Extract population and area for both states
area_maha = maha_data['Area (km2)'].iloc[0]
area_mp = mp_data['Area (km2)'].iloc[0]

population_maha = maha_data['Population'].iloc[0]
population_mp = mp_data['Population'].iloc[0]

# Compute population density
pop_density_maha = population_maha / area_maha
pop_density_mp = population_mp / area_mp

# Store results in a dictionary for comparison
pm25_comparison = {
    "Maharashtra": {
        "Average PM2.5": avg_pm25_maha,
        "Population Density": pop_density_maha
    },
    "Madhya Pradesh": {
        "Average PM2.5": avg_pm25_mp,
        "Population Density": pop_density_mp
    }
}

pollution_data['city'] = pollution_data['city'].str.lower()
pollution_data['Timestamp'] = pollution_data['Timestamp'].astype(str)
pollution_data_2023 = pollution_data[pollution_data['Timestamp'].str.contains("2023")]
avg_pm25_city = (pollution_data_2023.groupby('city')['PM2.5'].mean().reset_index())
most_polluted_city = avg_pm25_city.sort_values(by='PM2.5', ascending=False).iloc[0]['city']
most_polluted_city_data = pollution_data_2023[pollution_data_2023['city'] == most_polluted_city].copy()

most_polluted_city_data['PM2.5'] = most_polluted_city_data['PM2.5'].astype(float)
hazardous_days = most_polluted_city_data[most_polluted_city_data['PM2.5'] > 300]['Timestamp'].nunique()

total_days = most_polluted_city_data['Timestamp'].nunique()

percentage_hazardous_days = (hazardous_days / total_days) * 100

print(f"Most Polluted City in 2023: {most_polluted_city.capitalize()}")
print(f"Percentage of Hazardous Days: {percentage_hazardous_days:.2f}%")
